plementation of demonstrative projects reducing urban poor vulnerability. Objective 2: To develop and implement energy efficient technologies in housing construction insuring that a number of those improvements have equitable access and are adopted at district and municipality levels.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-02-01\",\"end-date\":\"2013-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Housing policy and administrative management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-02-01\",\"period_end\":\"2013-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2010-02-01\",\"value\":1019140}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":1014655,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":1019140,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"PK\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-966\":{\"title\":\"Medium Term Strategic And Institutional Plan, Focus Area 2\",\"description\":\"Thisproject shares the vision of the MTSIP, which is the help create by 2013 theconditions \\u201cto realize more sustainable urbanization, including efforts toarrest the growth of slums, and to set the stage for the subsequent reductionin and reversal of the number of slum dwellers worldwide\\u201d. Its specific goal is\\u201csustainable urbanization principles drive policy and practice.\\u201d\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-01-01\",\"end-date\":\"2012-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Urban development and management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-01-01\",\"period_end\":\"2012-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2010-01-01\",\"value\":2536303}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":2635463,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":2665106,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"WW\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-979\":{\"title\":\"Housing, Land And Property Interventions In Eastern Drc To Facilitate Return Of Idps And Refugees And Improve The Land Administration\",\"description\":\"To prevent local conflict in reducing the number of land dispute related to return of IDPs and refugeesTo locally develop and promote alternative dispute resolution mechanisms within local communitiesTo build capacities within the communities to deal with land disputes and land management through\\\"Land mediation centers\\\"\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-01-01\",\"end-date\":\"2012-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Urban development and management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-01-01\",\"period_end\":\"2012-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2010-01-01\",\"value\":1499378}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":1520635,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":1520636,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"CD\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-981\":{\"title\":\"Regional Competitiveness For The Tourism And Agro-Industrial Sectors In The Brunca Region, With Emphasis On The Creation Of Green And Decent Jobs And Proverty Reduction\",\"description\":\"UN-HABITAT will contribute directly to the achievement of the effect 1 \\u201cImproved environment for the development of competitive businesses in the Brunca region\\u201d. Specifically, the agency will promote the capacity building of the local governments in matters of strategic planning oriented towards the local competitiveness and the promotion of entrepreneurship in their respective territories.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-04-01\",\"end-date\":\"2013-06-30\",\"sector\":\"Urban development and management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-04-01\",\"period_end\":\"2013-06-30\",\"value_date\":\"2010-04-01\",\"value\":427010}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":424318,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":427010,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"CR\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-995\":{\"title\":\"Strengthening Municipal And Community Development, Phase Iii, In Lashkar Gar, Helmland, Afghanistan\",\"description\":\"This Project seeks to consolidate, strengthen, and expand the activities undertaken under Phase I and Phase II regarding community governance and settlement upgrading. This proposal is as such an extension of the current project Strengthening Municipal and Community Development Phase II funded by DFID. The Project aims to improve local governance and community development in Lashkar Gah city through community empowerment and improvement of the living conditions of people which will lead to improved trust between the local government and the people. Especially in the context of the stability and security continuation of showing tangible results to the population of Lashkar Gah is all the more important to gain the trust of the inhabitants in the local government and contribute to stability and development of the city.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-03-01\",\"end-date\":\"2013-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Housing policy and administrative management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-03-01\",\"period_end\":\"2013-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2010-03-01\",\"value\":7794859}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":7469833,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":7794859,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"AF\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-997\":{\"title\":\"Capacity Building For Land Conflict Management In South Sudan\",\"description\":\"The programme\\u2019s overall goal is to contribute to the more effective management of land-related disputes and conflicts in South Sudan. The programme will focus on critical interventions that will strengthen the capacity of key institutions to mitigate the risks of land-related disputes leading to conflict and to enable them to more effectively manage land disputes.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-04-01\",\"end-date\":\"2013-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Research\\/scientific institutions\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-04-01\",\"period_end\":\"2013-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2010-04-01\",\"value\":2570131}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":2400731,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":2400731,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"SS\",\"percentage\":100}]},\"41120-1000\":{\"title\":\"Youth Empowerment For Urban Development\",\"description\":\"Theoverall goal of the project is to improve the livelihoods of urban marginalizedyouth. This will through normative and programmatic activities enhance theirinclusion in governance, access to financial resources, and provision oftraining and information through dedicate urban space. The project will utilizean integrated approach that will focus on critical interventions to strengthenthe capacity of youth, local governments and strategic partner institutions toaddress urban youth issues.There are two main expected accomplishments(intermediate outcomes):Improvedlivelihoods for marginalised youth in urban slumsImproved inclusion of young people in governanceissues at all levels.There are foursub-expected accomplishments (immediate outcomes):Increasedaccess to financial resources by marginalised youth. Increased number of urban youth centres and training ofyouth in targeted cities. Increasedknowledge and sensitization of national local authorities in targeted countrieson matters of youth. Enhanced engagement of strategic partners (national, local,civil society, private sector and youth organizations) on matters of youth.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2012-01-01\",\"end-date\":\"2013-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Employment policy and administrative management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2012-01-01\",\"period_end\":\"2013-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2012-01-01\",\"value\":4218607}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":4342308,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":4464942,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"WW\",\"percentage\":100}]},\"41120-1004\":{\"title\":\"Urban And Productive Integrated Sustainable Settlements In El-Salvador\",\"description\":\"The Goal is to expand economic opportunities, especially for women and vulnerable groups while reducing the number of poor people living under the line of the poverty.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2009-12-01\",\"end-date\":\"2013-06-30\",\"sector\":\"Urban development and management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2009-12-01\",\"period_end\":\"2013-06-30\",\"value_date\":\"2009-12-01\",\"value\":1157740}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":1158110,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":1157740,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"SV\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-1007\":{\"title\":\"National Solidarity Programme(Nsp) Phase Iii, Afghanistan\",\"description\":\"The National Solidarity Programme (NSP) was created by the Government of Afghanistan to develop the ability of Afghan communities to identify, plan, manage and monitor their own development projects. NSP promotes a development paradigm whereby communities are empowered to make decisions and manage resources during all stages of the project cycle. The programme lays the foundation for a sustainable form of inclusive local governance, rural reconstruction, and poverty alleviation. NSP is the largest community development programme in the history of Afghanistan. Known in Dari as \\u201cHambastagi Milli\\u201d and in Pashtu as \\u201cMilli Paiwastoon\\u201d, it is based on the Afghan traditions of \\u201cAshar\\u201d (i.e. community members working together on a volunteer basis to improve community infrastructure) and \\u201cJirga\\u201d \\u2013 councils comprised of respected members of the community. Islamic values of unity, equity and justice are also encouraged. The following principles guide \\u201chow\\u201d the programme is implemented: participatory and inclusive decision-making processes; gender equity; transparency and accountability in the use of programme funds; and sustainability (including but not limited to requiring community contributions for operations and maintenance).  UN-HABITAT has been working with 3,258 communities in 47 districts of 9 provinces. The total number of 403 communities will be covered during the NSP Phase III under the UN-HABITAT\\u2019s facilitation.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-07-06\",\"end-date\":\"2015-09-30\",\"sector\":\"Housing policy and administrative management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-07-06\",\"period_end\":\"2015-09-30\",\"value_date\":\"2010-07-06\",\"value\":6470400}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":5287345,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":4757369,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"AF\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-1009\":{\"title\":\"Urban Household Sanitation Improvement Project, Lilongwe City, Malawi\",\"description\":\"The overall Goal is to improve the living conditions of the urban poor by facilitating access to affordable and environmentally friendly sanitation facilities, better sanitation practices, personal hygiene and food security through better management of human excrements.\",