",\"description\":\"The overall goal of the project is to assist the people affected by the recent floods in Pakistan, through:Increasing the provision of basic, adaptive shelters to vulnerable households and providingadequate shelters to extremely vulnerable households, especially female-headed households.Ensuring that returning male and female lDPs have equal rights to housing, land and properiy,security of tenure and equal access to inheritance.Reducing Incidence of mortality and morbidity due to waterborne diseases among women, girls,boys and men by providing safe drinking water and basic sanitation through the restoration andrehabilitation of water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) facilities for flood affected families.Enhancing sustainable community recovery and return through the rehabilitation of community infrastructure and cash for work programmes targeting debris removal\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2011-01-01\",\"end-date\":\"2015-03-31\",\"sector\":\"Disaster prevention and preparedness\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2011-01-01\",\"period_end\":\"2015-03-31\",\"value_date\":\"2011-01-01\",\"value\":44629670}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":44466694,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":44629670,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"PK\",\"percentage\":0}]},\"41120-1694\":{\"title\":\"Community-Driven Shelter Interventions In Sindth As Response To Pakistan\",\"description\":\"The people that have returned tothe communities so hard hit by the Pakistan 2010 Flood shall recover in ajoined, community based approach, to enable them to face the actual and futurethreats. Through this support the people shall, as they are eager to do, remainin their places of origin.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-12-29\",\"end-date\":\"2012-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Disaster prevention and preparedness\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-12-29\",\"period_end\":\"2012-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2010-12-29\",\"value\":2688335}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":2544761,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":2688335,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"PK\",\"percentage\":34},{\"iso2\":\"PH\",\"percentage\":33},{\"iso2\":\"LK\",\"percentage\":33}]},\"41120-1695\":{\"title\":\"Post-Conflict Assistance To West Timorese Women And Indegenous Community\",\"description\":\"The overall objective of the project subscribes to the EU guidelines, i.e. to improve the social-political integration of uprooted people as citizens. The specific objective is to provide training, capacity-building and advocacy interventions for local administrations and local parliamentarians to better respond to the needs of uprooted women and IDPs in West Timor.  This objective should be framed with the aim of the Aid to Uprooted People and aims of the concurrent post-conflict programmes within the policies of the Indonesian government. Widespread conflict and displacement affected several regions of Indonesia, including Maluku, Central Sulawesi and West Timor, in the period 1998 and 2002. Healing and integration are still ongoing. In the case of West Timor the violent post-referendum phase in East Timor caused a large influx of pro-Indonesia fighters and sympathizers and their families, and other caught up. The influx took place in areas where traditional community conflicts had simmered for long, and where indigenous communities clashed with new elites, whether military or economic. Many of these local tensions were suppressed during the Suharto era, but erupted (and where often intentionally ignited) as of 1997. The East Timor crisis, however, caused a full blown political displacement crisis in West Timor.   The Indonesian Government expects that overall policies should now focus on \\u2018moving ahead\\u2019, on sustainable development. Conflict prevention and peace building was written in into national policies. The last National Medium Term Development Programme (2005-2009) called for a \\u2018safe and peaceful, just and democratic Indonesia with better welfare\\u2019. The present five-year plan is more specific, and calls for a special development focus on zones which are least developed, frontier, outer or post-conflict. In NTT, the government states that restitution issues have been dealt with and that peace consolidation is not at the order. Displaced people should become full citizens; they should be part of communities of citizens.        The present calls of the EU look for closure as well. The Aid to Uprooted People programme was delivering direct assistance to people affected by conflict and displacement. To phase out, in line with the expectations of the Indonesian Government, it now addresses the last groups of uprooted people which have failed to find for themselves or find assistance from others for a more secure future. These \\u2018most vulnerable\\u2019 are often women, children, female headed households and certain groups of indigenous people (or local people in hosting communities in general) which were also affected by the displacement crisis. The first 2010 call delivered assistance directly to communities. The second call was for improved monitoring and early warning capacity. The third and present call wants to assist local governments and elected officials to also deliver assistance, now and in the future\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2010-12-31\",\"end-date\":\"2014-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Disaster prevention and preparedness\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2010-12-31\",\"period_end\":\"2014-12-31\",\"value_date\":\"2010-12-31\",\"value\":1234721}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":1125180,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":1198791,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"TL\",\"percentage\":100}]},\"41120-1697\":{\"title\":\"Un-Habitat Support To Asia Development Bank (Adb) City Development Initiative For Asian Cities\",\"description\":\"To contribute to cities having institutionalised high quality Capital Investment Project Prioritisation (CIPP) reports, Pre-Feasibility Study (PFS) and capital infrastructure investment programming approaches which contribute to improvements in city environments, governance, poverty reduction and mitigation\\/adaptation to climate change impacts\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2011-01-12\",\"end-date\":\"2012-03-31\",\"sector\":\"Urban development and management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2011-01-12\",\"period_end\":\"2012-03-31\",\"value_date\":\"2011-01-12\",\"value\":400000}],\"transactions\":[{\"code\":\"E\",\"value\":450000,\"description\":\"Total expenditure to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"},{\"code\":\"IF\",\"value\":466896,\"description\":\"Total income to date\",\"date\":\"2015-04-01\"}],\"countries\":[{\"iso2\":\"CN\",\"percentage\":25},{\"iso2\":\"ID\",\"percentage\":25},{\"iso2\":\"PH\",\"percentage\":25},{\"iso2\":\"LK\",\"percentage\":25}]},\"41120-1700\":{\"title\":\"Enhancement Of Technical Cooperation Towards Environmentaly Sustainability\",\"description\":\"The goal of the project is to achieve environmentally sustainable development of Asia and the Pacific region while building capacity of the partners in the region and develop strong partnerships between Japan and countries in the region through international assistance and technical cooperation.\",\"currency\":\"USD\",\"status\":\"Implementation\",\"start-date\":\"2011-04-01\",\"end-date\":\"2012-12-31\",\"sector\":\"Urban development and management\",\"budget\":[{\"period_start\":\"2011-04-01\",\"period_end\":\"2012-12-31\